_comment: Spawn quality log. Each event records one spawn decision and its outcome.

_fields.frontier: which frontier question this advances (or null)
_fields.two_phase: true if discovery agent preceded partition agents (P-119)
_fields.findings_per_agent: count of distinct findings per agent [n1, n2, ...]
_fields.cross_agent_unique: findings only possible from multi-agent comparison

spawn_events.task_description: F71 test: 2-agent partition on architecture question (method vs data decomposition)
missed_dimensions: architecture dimension found only by single agent post-hoc
spawn_events.notes: Partition without discovery failed. 2-agent split missed architecture dimension that single agent found. 2.3x tool call overhead for no marginal novelty. Source: P-119, L-114.

spawn_events.task_description: F107 genesis feedback: 3 reporter agents on genesis atom usage
spawn_events.notes: High convergence on genesis atoms (all 3 reporters agree). Convergent density confirms unanimous findings. Session-1-only limitation identified: belief-tracking and distill-protocol ignored in S1 but load-bearing at S3+. Source: f107-genesis-ablation.md.

spawn_events.task_description: F104 personality test: skeptic + explorer on F76/F100 analysis
spawn_events.notes: Complementary personalities produced qualitatively different outputs: skeptic defined minimum evidence bar (n=3 bugs insufficient, collinear with contract-type), explorer generated 5 new mechanisms to test (gofail density, error topology, temporal contract). Together = correct epistemic state. Explorer alone = unchallenged hypotheses. Skeptic alone = analysis paralysis. Source: P-116, L-111.

spawn_events.task_description: F103: 3-agent colony on repo analysis (dutch + complexity_ising_idea)
spawn_events.notes: NK found structure findings, EH found error handling patterns, Verification found cross-agent convergence signal. 2 findings were only possible because multiple agents compared notes. 3rd agent (verification) added 1 unique cross-agent finding. Wall-time 2.2x faster than sequential. Source: P-114, L-110.

spawn_events.task_description: F103 test 3: ilkerloan multi-domain analysis (NK + EH + legal + verification)
spawn_events.notes: Multi-domain sparse-docs case: 4/4 convergent findings = highest confidence signal. Legal analyst found Box 3 tax (EUR 432/year) and Brussels I jurisdiction gap — impossible for NK or EH agents to find. Cross-agent convergence on jurisdiction issue from both NK and legal perspectives. Multiplicative advantage confirmed. Source: P-114, L-110, f103-ilkerloan-multi-domain.md.

spawn_events.task_description: Background compression agent: proxy K MDL pass (HUMAN.md, FRONTIER.md, PRINCIPLES.md, maintenance.py)
spawn_events.outcome: proxy K 26034→23383 (-10.2%), new floor below S77 floor
spawn_events.notes: Context isolation spawn: task too large for main context (needed to read+edit 10+ files). Single-agent isolation prevents bloating parent context. Measurable outcome (proxy K reduction). Spawn type: isolation.

spawn_events.task_description: F117 nk-analyze-go v0.1.0 extraction: 566L Go tools → installable lib (65 tests)
spawn_events.notes: Isolation spawn: lib extraction is well-scoped, context-heavy (reading 566L source + writing 300L lib + 200L tests). No cross-agent comparison needed — correctness is binary (tests pass/fail). Spawn type: isolation.

spawn_events.task_description: F117 10-tool audit: assess 10 coordination tools for lib extractability (ROI formula)
spawn_events.outcome: P-168 ROI formula: size × domain_independence / coupling; 7/10 not extractable, 3 extractable
spawn_events.notes: Data partition spawn: 10 separable candidates, each needs independent assessment. Single-agent sufficient for audit scale (n=10 manageable). Produced P-168 and L-181. Spawn type: coverage (collapsed to 1 agent due to manageable scale).

spawn_events.outcome: 4/5 support sub-agents; ~60% tool-agnostic; hooks are hard bridge; L-187, P-169 produced
spawn_events.notes: Data partition spawn: 5 tools each needing independent research (docs/capabilities). Context isolation: needed web research + file writing, cleanly scoped. Produced L-187 + P-169 + AGENTS.md + GEMINI.md. Spawn type: coverage (collapsed to 1 agent, scale manageable).

spawn_events.task_description: F115 paper re-swarm: check docs/PAPER.md drift against S73-S94 developments
spawn_events.outcome: PAPER.md v0.1→v0.2: 5 stale sections updated, 3 new observed mechanisms added
spawn_events.notes: Isolation spawn: paper re-swarm requires reading 5+ files + writing changes + committing. Context-heavy, well-defined success criteria (paper reflects current state). No cross-agent comparison needed. Spawn type: isolation.
